gomodel:SYNGO_1136  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this reference paper, Jahn et al. investigate the distribution of synaptophysin by subcellular fractionation, immunoblotting and immunostaining of coronal sections of rat brain. Additionally, solubilization studies (with Triton X-114 phase separation) and controlled proteolysis of intact and solubilized synaptic vesicles reveal that synaptophysin is an integral vesicular protein.\n\n2/9/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods:\nIsolation of Synaptic Vesicles. Isolation of synaptic vesicles\nwas performed by the procedure of Nagy et al. (16) as\nadapted by Huttner et al. (12) with minor modifications. All\nprocedures were carried out at 4°C. Briefly, cerebral cortices\nof 14 rats were homogenized in 150 ml of 0.32 M sucrose\ncontaining 0.1 mM phenylmethylsulfonyl fluoride by 10\nstrokes at 900 rpm in a glass/teflon homogenizer.\n\nAbstract:\nA protein with an apparent molecular mass of\n38,000 daltons designated p38 was found in synaptic vesicles\nfrom rat brain." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1136" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

